data.name: HowToUseTextbox.Text
data.value:
Getting Started:
The files are located in your game root, in one of these folders. (Game root: Steam\steamapps\common\Devil May Cry 5\) 941953 = DMC1 Tracks 941954 = DMC2 Tracks 941955 = DMC3 Tracks 941956 = DMC4 Tracks You'll want to extract the .pak to get the unpacked files.
Tutorial on how to extract .pak here: https://www.tapatalk.com/groups/infernalworks/tutorial-how-to-extract-pak-files-t3913.html
re_dlc_000\natives\x64\streaming\sound\wwise\ contains: bgm_dlc_set_0X.pck.3.x64
re_dlc_000\natives\x64\sound\wwise contains: bgm_dlc_set_0X.pck.3.x64 and bgm_dlc_set_0X.bnk.2.x64
bgm_dlc_set_0X = Which DLC, 01 = DMC1, 03 = DMC3, ect.
Since both folder locations contains an exact same file name, I name one of them as 'streaming' file and 'sound' file. The streaming file is the one which actually contains the music inside it. The 'sound' file just the header file. The .bnk.2.x64 inside the 'sound' folder, is the one that contains all the loops in it.
This tool should only be used after importing your music tracks using wwise and wwiseutil-gui.
Tutorial on that here: (Ignore the Hex Editor/Replacing Audio/Limitations Sections) http://residentevilmodding.boards.net/thread/10211/method-audio-modding
This tool automatically does the header offsets and lets you configure the loop points with ease. No hex editing required.
Using the Tool:
The WEM ID is the Music Track that you're replacing. When importing the tracks using wwiseutil-gui the WEM ID is listed under 'Id'. (You use wwiseutil-gui on the 'streaming' file, in case you need to check the ID.)
Start of Song, Loop Start, Loop End, and Total Length are all recorded in milliseconds. So if you want the start of a song to be at 17 seconds, it'd look like 17232. 17 Seconds, 232 Milliseconds.
Start of Song is the very beginning of when you want the song to be played. This lets you skip to a point of the song you want.
Loop Start, Loop End, and Total Length is self explanatory.
Swap Sections is an oddity to me, sometimes the tracks have their code backwards so having this checked will input it backwards.
If your music doesn't start / loop properly initially try toggling the Swap Sections checkbox.
Tool Created By: Kuroha Saenoki and Zealot Tormunds
After you create your music mod, use fluffyquacks mod manager: http://residentevilmodding.boards.net/thread/10142/modding-pak-files
